  &lt;p id="i0doJf"&gt;AT&amp;amp;T has announced a &lt;a href="https://about.att.com/story/2024/internet-backup-for-consumers.html"&gt;new feature called Internet Backup&lt;/a&gt; that will automatically switch from a home’s wired internet to a cellular connection through a nearby smartphone should its fiber service experience a disruption. The feature is offered at no additional charge to customers with AT&amp;amp;T Fiber service and an “eligible AT&amp;amp;T unlimited postpaid wireless plan” with unlimited data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="AHpI8R"&gt;Internet Backup is being rolled out to customers starting next week through a software update to AT&amp;amp;T’s BGW320 Wi-Fi gateways. The company says that fiber customers using different hardware “may need to upgrade to access this feature.”&lt;/p&gt;
